docs.abstract: Pocket-size medallions once given by commanders have been adapted for civilian government agencies from fire departments to the E.P.A.
docs.snippet: Pocket-size medallions once given by commanders have been adapted for civilian government agencies from fire departments to the E.P.A.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Scott Pruitt, the administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, has proposed a redesign of the agency’s commemorative coin, an adaptation of longstanding “challenge coins” exchanged among American troops. From a military drinking tradition to civilian government agencies, here is how the coins have evolved and proliferated.

headline.main: Morale, Allegiance and Drinking: How Military Challenge Coins Evolved and Spread

docs.abstract: The House speaker, Paul D. Ryan, still projects power, but back home in Wisconsin, he is facing political challengers from both the right and the left.
docs.snippet: The House speaker, Paul D. Ryan, still projects power, but back home in Wisconsin, he is facing political challengers from both the right and the left.
docs.lead_paragraph: JANESVILLE, Wis. — When dozens of high school students from across Wisconsin marched through his hometown, chanting his name and demanding new gun control laws, Paul D. Ryan, the House speaker, was not around to hear them, having just wrapped up a trip to the Czech Republic.

headline.main: Can Paul Ryan Be Defeated? Maybe Not, but His Race Is ‘a Circus’

docs.abstract: Todd Ricketts is expected to be the new finance chairman for the Republican National Committee, replacing the disgraced casino magnate Steve Wynn.
docs.snippet: Todd Ricketts is expected to be the new finance chairman for the Republican National Committee, replacing the disgraced casino magnate Steve Wynn.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Todd Ricketts, a co-owner of the Chicago Cubs, is expected to be named the new finance chairman of the Republican National Committee, replacing the casino magnate Steve Wynn, who was pushed out amid allegations of serious sexual abuse, three Republican officials said on Tuesday.

headline.main: Chicago Cubs Co-owner Ricketts Expected to Head G.O.P. Fund-raising
headline.print_headline: A Cubs Owner Tapped to Lead G.O.P. Finance
